Overleden","1300–1355":"1300–1355","1314":"1314","Abt 1300":"circa 1300","Abt 1355":"circa 1355","1344":"1344","1300":"1300","1355":"1355","about 1334":"circa 1334","1370":"1370","after 1355":"na 1355","Cromartyshire, Scotland":"Cromartyshire, Schotland","Scotland":"Schotland","Kintail, Ross & Cromarty, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Schotland","Lochbroom, Ross and Cromarty, Scotland":"Cromartyshire, Schotland","Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Schotland","Lochbroom, Ross, Scotland":"Ross and Cromarty, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1300–after 1355":"about 1300–after 1355","1314–Female":"1314–Deceased","1344–1370":"1344–1370","1355–Male":"1355–Deceased","1300–1355":"1300–1355","1314":"1314","Abt 1300":"about 1300","Abt 1355":"about 1355","1344":"1344","1300":"1300","1355":"1355","about 1334":"about 1334","1370":"1370","after 1355":"after 1355","Cromartyshire, Scotland":"Cromartyshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Kintail, Ross & Cromarty, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland","Lochbroom, Ross and Cromarty, Scotland":"Cromartyshire, Scotland","Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland","Lochbroom, Ross, Scotland":"Ross and Cromarty, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"MacAulay","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish (mainly Ross and Cromarty and Inverness):","from Gaelic <b>Mac Amhalghaidh</b> ‘son of <i>Amhalghadh</i>’, an Old Gaelic personal name of unexplained etymology. Compare the Irish form   McAuley  , also Manx   Kewley  ,   Cowley  , and   Callow  .","from Gaelic <b>Mac Amhlaoibh</b> ‘son of <i>Amhlao(i)bh</i>’, Gaelic form of the Old Norse personal name <i>Óláfr</i> (see   Olafsen  ). Compare   McAuliffe  ."],"variants":[{"name":"McAulay","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Macaulay  . Compare the Irish form   McAuley  ."]},{"name":"McCauley","meanings":["Scottish (Dumbartonshire) and Irish (Westmeath): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Amhalghaidh</b> ‘son of <i>Amhalghadh</i>’, a personal name of uncertain origin. The best known family of <i>Mac Amhalghaidh</i> is from Westmeath, and there were families called <i>Mac Amhlaoibh</i> in counties Cork and Fermanagh (a branch of the Maguires), as well as a family in southwest Scotland which has migrated to Ulster. Compare the Scottish form   Macaulay  .","Scottish (Hebrides) and Irish (Fermanagh): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Amhlaoibh</b> or <b>Mac Amhlaidh</b> ‘son of Olaf’, from Gaelic forms of the Old Norse personal name <i>Áleifr</i>, <i>Óláfr</i> (see   Olafsen  ). Compare   McAuliffe  ."]},{"name":"McAuley","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Declan.","Irish: variant of   McCauley  . Compare the Scottish form   Macaulay  ."]}]},{"name":"Duncan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Donnchadh , also used among people without Scottish connections. This was the name of a 7th-century Scottish saint (abbot of Iona) and two medieval kings of Scotland. The final ‐<i>n</i> in the Anglicized form seems to be the result of confusion with the Gaelic word <i>ceann</i> ‘head’ in the Latinized form <i>Duncanus</i>.  Compare Irish  Donagh ."],"variants":[{"name":"Donnchadh","meanings":["Gaelic: compound of Old Celtic <i>donn</i> ‘brown’ + <i>chadh</i> ‘chief’ or ‘noble’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Duncan MacAulay of Lochbroom was born about 1300, in Cromartyshire, Scotland. He married Katherine Murchison about 1334, in Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died after 1355, in Scotland, and was buried in Scotland."},"et":{"Abt 1300–after 1355":"umbes 1300–pärast 1355","1314–Female":"1314–Surnud","1344–1370":"1344–1370","1355–Male":"1355–Surnud","1300–1355":"1300–1355","1314":"1314","Abt 1300":"umbes 1300","Abt 1355":"umbes 1355","1344":"134